I"q<h1 id="goals-for-this-summer">Goals for this summer</h1>

<p>5 days ago marked the official end of my IB diploma (at least all the work that I will need to do to receive my diploma) and also hopefully started a wonderful summer. Since this is most likely the last summer of which I will have no internships, work or big exams to study for, it means this will likely be the last summer that I can do whatever the fuck I want.</p>

<p>SO, in order to make this summer productive, I’m going to write a list down now of things that I want to do before September where first year of university starts.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Re-run <a href="https://www.instagram.com/superficial.visuals/">@superficial.visuals</a> with Winston my dear friend. Instead of having a theme or whatever, I plan to just dump what I enjoy and also use it as a place for my digital-art.</li>
  <li>Learn how to use Blender to create 3D art. I personally really enjoy art that look realistic but clearly defy the laws of Physics.</li>
  <li>Code at least 2 side projects. I already know what I want to do, but I will release the details later when I am more comfortable :)</li>
  <li>Write an EP. Been talking about this forever now — this summer’s gotta be the one where it finally happens.</li>
  <li>Nail and record with my jazz band at a studio again.</li>
  <li>Get fit again lol.</li>
</ol>

<p>For now, those are my biggest priorities and I plan to use this blog to update my progress throughout summer.</p>

<h1 id="progress-mid-week-1-of-summer2021">Progress: Mid-Week 1 of Summer2021</h1>

<h2 id="photography--purchased-my-first-ever-professional-camera">Photography — purchased my first-ever professional camera</h2>

<p>I bought a new camera recently so I’ve been out taking a lot of photos, experimenting with this somewhat unfamiliar medium.</p>

<h2 id="javascript-html-and-css--learning-the-fundamentals">Javascript, HTML and CSS — learning the fundamentals</h2>

<p>Succesefully made my own private website (just locally hosted, so you guys won’t be able to see it). I hope to be able to create responsive websites using Bootstrap by the end of today and explore different JS animation scripts by the end of this week.</p>

<p>Though web design is not computer science so learning all of this would not help my CS degree next year, I still think its a useful skill to have. Besides, its another creative outlet that works nicely with my Photoshopping experience.</p>

<h2 id="blender--created-my-first-ever-piece-of-cg-art">Blender — created my first-ever piece of CG art</h2>

<p>Created my first ever piece of render art. I followed Blender Guru’s iconic <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=TPrnSACiTJ4">beginner CG donut tutorial</a> but got bored and don’t really care for the final outcome, so instead I found another <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Vt-_Htl-R90">environment tutorial</a> which I ultimately edited into my first render artwork ever.</p>

